### 12. Create an EF Core migration and apply it

Run: `dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate --project ShipmentTracker` and `dotnet ef database update --project ShipmentTracker`

If `dotnet-ef` tool is not installed, install it first: `dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef`

### 13. Build and verify

Run `dotnet build ShipmentTracker.sln` from the solution directory.

## Important Notes
- The server project already has a reference to the Client project (template does this).
- The Client `.csproj` needs `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly` package (already in template).
- Make sure the `IShipmentService` interface is accessible from both projects — define it in the Client project.
- The server `Program.cs` already imports `ShipmentTracker.Client.Pages` so it has access to Client types.

Please implement all of these steps. Create all the files, modify existing ones, delete template pages, and verify the build passes.
